1. **Resource Efficiency**: Single conditional writer instance shared across all mutations instead of creating multiple writers
2. **Thread Pool Reuse**: One configurable thread pool instead of multiple
3. **Lazy Initialization**: Using memoized Supplier means read-only stores never create the writer
4. **Batch Processing**: BatchSeeder demonstrates efficient batch mutation submission
5. **Proper Cleanup**: Close method ensures proper resource cleanup when FATE shuts down

